<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>closed case • open-and-shut case</xh5><p> <i>closed case—</i>a legal case that has been decided: Trying to reopen a <u>closed case</u> is a very difficult, time consuming (and usually expensive) process.</p><p> <i>open-and-shut case—</i>a legal case that is easily settled or decided: The jury feels this is an <u>open-and-shut case</u> but Sir John experiences doubts.</p> </entry>
